Subject: [PATCH 3/3] feat(web): track generation jobs with status and captured
 logs
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- web/jobs.py: in-process JobManager — worker threads with a concurrency
  cap, queued/running/succeeded/failed lifecycle, per-job log files under
  .mp/jobs/ with tail retrieval, bounded in-memory history
- server.py: POST /api/jobs/{provider}/{account_id} now returns a tracked
  job record; new GET /api/jobs and GET /api/jobs/{id} (with log tail)
- frontend: Jobs tab with status pills, auto-refresh and inline log view;
  per-account 'gerar' button on the YouTube/Twitter tabs

Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
